{
  "_meta": {
    "country": "Spain",
    "collectedAt": "2026-05-05",
    "method": "Web research across the official directories of Comunidad Buddhista Soto Zen (sotozen.es), Sotoshu Europe (sotozen.com), Asociación Zen Internacional / Kosen Sangha (zen-deshimaru.com, zenkan.com), Templo Seikyuji affiliates, Camino Medio (caminomedio.org), Instituto Internacional Zen de España (Lam Te / Rinzai), Kwan Um Europe (kwanumeurope.org, boricentro.kwanumzen.es), Comunidad Budista del Interser (tnhspain.com), Buddhistdoor en Español Catalonia/Balearic directory, and the IRIZ Hanazono University zen centers list. Each entry was cross-verified against at least one institutional/network directory.",
    "coverageEstimate": "Strong coverage of the four main networks (Sōtō CBSZ, AZI/Kosen-Deshimaru, Seikyuji/Camino Medio, Kwan Um) and the Plum Village lay sangha network. Sanbō Zen presence in Spain is a single hub (Zendo Betania + offshoots). Rinzai presence is limited (Vietnamese Lam Te lineage via IIZE). No active Ōbaku presence located. Plum Village lay sanghas are listed selectively (representative subset of ~50 groups; many are home-based without a fixed dojo).",
    "knownGaps": [
      "Some Plum Village 'sanghas' meet in private homes without a fixed practice place — not all are listed",
      "Ōbaku-shū has no documented active presence in Spain",
      "White Plum Asanga has no resident Spanish teacher / fixed center",
      "A few small Soto groups (e.g. Mokusan Dojo Madrid sub-groups) may overlap with parent dojos",
      "Phone-only / email-only contacts dropped where no institutional URL was confirmed",
      "Address not always public (privacy of host venues); kept null where unknown but URL+source confirmed"
    ]
  },
